  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/5081",
  "title": "feat(html): introduce `html` templating",
  "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR introduces `html` templating in InstantSearch.js.\r\n\r\nThis allows InstantSearch.js users to pass templates as HTML strings safely, with easier access to exposed data, and with an easier API to set up events.\r\n\r\n[**Try this live**](https://codesandbox.io/s/instantsearch-js-forked-xfoouv?file=/src/app.js) | [**Read RFC**](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch-rfcs/blob/master/accepted/html-templating-instantsearch.md)\r\n\r\n>The current sandbox needs to import `@babel/runtime` for now, this will be fixed.\r\n\r\n```js\r\ninstantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n  // ...\r\n  templates: {\r\n    item(hit, { html, components, sendEvent }) {\r\n      return html`<article>\r\n        <h2>${components.Highlight({ hit, attribute: 'name' })}</h2>\r\n        <p>${components.Snippet({ hit, attribute: 'description' })}</p>\r\n        <button\r\n          onClick=\"${() => sendEvent('conversion', hit, 'Product Added')}\"\r\n        >\r\n          Add to cart\r\n        </button>\r\n      </article>`;\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Note:** For now, the feature doesn't work in [`pagination`](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/pagination/js/) and [`geoSearch`](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/geo-search/js/). `pagination` will be handled separately, and `geoSearch` will be tackled later (at most when we deprecate Hogan.js) depending on complexity and demand.\r\n\r\n## Tests\r\n\r\nTesting this feature involves testing templates in ~20 widgets. That's a lot of files, so I did it in a [separate PR](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/5087).",
